### Summary of Core Topics, Concepts, Principles, and Equations

#### 1. **Natural Language Processing (NLP) Basics**
- **Levels of Language Processing**: Lexical, Syntactic, Semantic, Discourse, Pragmatic
- **Ambiguity**: Lexical, Syntactic, Semantic
- **POS Tagging**: Part-of-Speech Tagging, challenges with ambiguous words
- **Morphological Analysis**: Stemming, Lemmatization, Over-stemming, Under-stemming

#### 2. **Finite State Automata (FSA) and Finite State Transducers (FST)**
- **FSA**: Recognizes patterns in input strings
- **FST**: Recognizes patterns and produces corresponding outputs

#### 3. **Hidden Markov Models (HMM)**
- **Forward Algorithm**: Initializes α1(i), calculates αt(i) recursively, sums over final states
- **Viterbi Algorithm**: Finds the optimal state sequence
- **Baum-Welch Algorithm**: Parameter estimation in unsupervised learning
- **Backward Algorithm**: Computes posterior probabilities

#### 4. **Conditional Random Fields (CRF)**
- **Feature Combination**: Handles complex feature combinations better than HMM

#### 5. **Dependency Parsing**
- **Maximum Spanning Tree**: Calculating the score of the maximum spanning tree
- **Evaluation Metrics**: Unlabeled Attachment Score (UAS), Label Accuracy Score (LS)

#### 6. **Semantic Role Labeling**
- **Semantic Roles**: Agent, Theme, Beneficiary, Instrument

#### 7. **Context-Free Grammar (CFG)**
- **Chomsky Normal Form (CNF)**: Required for CKY parsing algorithm

#### 8. **Named Entity Recognition (NER)**
- **Overlapping Entities**: Scenarios where entities overlap

#### 9. **Clustering in NLP**
- **Applications**: Grouping similar entities in NER, Unsupervised POS tagging, Word clustering into syntactic categories

#### 10. **Evaluation Metrics**
- **Precision**: Proportion of correct semantic roles identified
- **Recall**: Proportion of correct dependency relations retrieved

### Equations

#### Probability Calculations in HMM
- **Emission Probability**: \( P(\text{word} | \text{tag}) \)
- **Transition Probability**: \( P(\text{tag}_2 | \text{tag}_1) \)
- **Combined Probability**:
  \[
  P(\text{tag}_1 \rightarrow \text{tag}_2 \rightarrow \text{tag}_3) = P(\text{word}_1 | \text{tag}_1) \times P(\text{tag}_2 | \text{tag}_1) \times P(\text{word}_2 | \text{tag}_2) \times P(\text{tag}_3 | \text{tag}_2) \times P(\text{word}_3 | \text{tag}_3)
  \]

#### Evaluation Metrics
- **Precision**:
  \[
  \text{Precision} = \frac{\text{Number of correct predictions}}{\text{Total number of predictions}}
  \]
- **Recall**:
  \[
  \text{Recall} = \frac{\text{Number of correct predictions}}{\text{Total number of actual positives}}
  \]

